Anthony Corrales of New Jersey has filed a suit claiming he was almost killed by a retired NYPD officer last June . 
  He claims he was driving with his wife and daughter in the Queens section of New York City when a car cut in front of him and refused to change lanes . 
  He then claims he got out of the car to get the car's license plate number and was driven for several blocks by the driver - Robert Muller . 
  The incident occurred outside the Resorts World Casino in Queens . 
  Muller was then let off the hook by fellow cops . 
 